channel.title: What the hell do these mean? (pics)
channel.description:
This appears in my runserver thing every once in a while..:
I'm talking about after where it says Zer0z7 signed on. [IMG]http://i169.photobucket.com/albums/u221/zer0z7/error.jpg[/img]
EDIT: Also, I meant to put this last night but the forums were down.. every once in a while the server boots everyone, but we can all log right back in a second later and if you were fighting like a monster and it had half hp, it'd still have half. (anyone know a solution to all the server boots?..)
This is what I read when that happens, and this is on the MoparScape client not the runserver: [IMG]http://i169.photobucket.com/albums/u221/zer0z7/errormate.jpg[/img] I see this on other servers to when this happens.

item.title: What the hell do these mean? (pics)
item.dc:creator: @Simply_Z3R0 Simply Z3R0
item.description:
@Simply_Z3R0 wrote:

[quote=“jehanne, post:5, topic:62106”]the server makes a log of all trades. in your case it saves at C:/documents and settings/moparnarb/desktop/narb 4 beta/logs/

but that place doesnt exist at your computer. just edit wher it saves.[/quote]

Thanks everyone… doesn’t sound like a big problem and
how do I edit where it saves?

I’m new at servers[br][size=1]Posted on: February 26, 2007, 03:01:56 PM[/size][hr]and my trade logs… they are in a different file but they appear there too…

I just checked and it was trades from last night.[br][size=1]Posted on: February 26, 2007, 03:07:02 PM[/size][hr][quote=“jehanne, post:7, topic:62106”][quote author=CRIPZ Chick link=topic=89603.msg945184#msg945184 date=1172533901]
It shows what every one is spawning and if any player types :: (and then a command) It will show you who typed it or who crashed the server and all.
[/quote]

nobody typed anything. its just a wrong path in client.java[/quote]

Is this bad… will it effect anything? and how do I fix it?
